
README Blueprint: K3s for Beginners
1. Introduction

What is Kubernetes and why it exists (the container orchestration problem)
What is K3s and how it differs from full K8s (lightweight, single binary, SQLite vs etcd)
Who this guide is for and prerequisites


2. Core Concepts (Conceptual Layer)
Start with mental models before any commands. Cover:

Cluster — the whole system (control plane + nodes)
Node — a machine (VM or physical) in the cluster
Pod — smallest deployable unit, wraps one or more containers
Namespace — logical isolation within a cluster
Label & Selectors — how resources find each other


