5. Workloads (The "What runs")
Each section: what it is → when to use it → minimal YAML example

Deployment — stateless apps, rolling updates
StatefulSet — databases, ordered identity
DaemonSet — runs on every node (log collectors, monitoring)
Job / CronJob — one-off or scheduled tasks


6. Networking

Service types: ClusterIP, NodePort, LoadBalancer
Ingress — HTTP routing (K3s ships Traefik by default)
DNS — how pods find each other by name
NetworkPolicy — optional traffic rules


7. Configuration & Secrets

ConfigMap — non-sensitive config (env vars, files)
Secret — sensitive data (base64, not encrypted by default — mention this gotcha)
How to mount them into pods (env vs volume)


8. Storage

Volume — ephemeral, tied to pod lifecycle
PersistentVolume (PV) — cluster-level storage resource
PersistentVolumeClaim (PVC) — pod's request for storage
K3s default: local-path provisioner


